A group of disgruntled artists barred staff from leaving the building and demanded answers on COVID-19 relief funds. eNCA/Khayelihle Khumalo JOHANNESBURG - Local artists have been promised their COVID-19 relief fund payments will be paid on Friday. A group of disgruntled performers blocked the exit of the Gauteng Arts and Culture Department in downtown Johannesburg on Thursday. They were demanding answers on relief funds. READ: Disgruntled artists demand answers on COVID-19 relief funds The situation was resolved after a meeting between the artists and officials. Another round of meetings will be held next week. The department has earmarked approximately R28-million to fund artists.